2.3 Refusal rules enforced inside the userscript
Drop any envelope from Worker C that contains a Cookie: header — the userscript is not a cookie-injection primitive. The browser supplies cookies via credentials: 'include'; Worker C must never tell the userscript what cookie to send.
Refuse any inbound envelope whose method/path tries to hit api.anthropic.com, console.anthropic.com, platform.claude.com, openclaude.111724.xyz, cfc.aroic.workers.dev, aroic.workers.dev, or 111724.xyz — these are either Anthropic's first-party API surface (out of scope for the userscript path) or the four CoCoDem C2 hosts.
Refuse any inbound envelope whose body contains a top-level system field exceeding 64 KB — mutation cap.
Never read document.cookie — the override only ever sets credentials: 'include'.
Never call GM_cookie, chrome.cookies.*, or any other cookie-reading API.
Restrict @match to claude.ai/* — no *.anthropic.com/*, no localhost, no <all_urls>.
