5. Worker C inject_canary mode (the 5th mutation mode, USER SET, default OFF)
Per READ 2.txt and the operator answer ("USER SET. DEFAULT OFF"), Worker C's mutation engine implements 5 modes:

Mode	Behavior
passthrough (default)	Log only, forward unchanged. KV log records original_system and final_system (identical).
strip	Delete body.system entirely. KV log records final_system: null.
replace	Substitute with env.WC_INJECT_SYSTEM string.
prepend / append	Wrap original system prompt with operator-controlled prefix/suffix.
inject_canary	USER SET, DEFAULT OFF. Inject env.WC_CANARY string (or WC-CANARY-<crypto.randomUUID()> if unset) into the system prompt. Worker C records canary_set: <hash>; the userscript watches the rendered DOM via checkCanaryInDOM() and reports canary_echoed: true over WS if the canary string appears in document.body.innerText. The combination is what produces the wire-evidence-trail for the VDP report.
The default OFF state is enforced by WC_MODE = env.WC_MODE || 'passthrough' and if (WC_MODE === 'inject_canary' && !env.WC_CANARY_OPT_IN) return passthrough() — three layers of opt-in: the env var WC_MODE, the env var WC_CANARY_OPT_IN=true, and the operator-provided canary string. If any one is missing, the mode falls back to passthrough.

